<li id="cite_note-0"><b><a href="#cite_ref-0" title="">^</a></b> J J O'Connor and E F Robertson, <a href="http://www-history.mcs.st-andrews.ac.uk/HistTopics/Ring_theory.html" class="external text" title="http://www-history.mcs.st-andrews.ac.uk/HistTopics/Ring_theory.html" rel="nofollow"><i>The development of Ring Theory</i></a>, September 2004.</li>
<li id="cite_note-1"><b><a href="#cite_ref-1" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="" id="CITEREFFrickeWeber1924">Fricke, Robert; <a href="/wiki/Heinrich_Martin_Weber" title="Heinrich Martin Weber">Weber, Heinrich Martin</a> (1924), <i><a href="http://resolver.sub.uni-goettingen.de/purl?PPN234788267" class="external text" title="http://resolver.sub.uni-goettingen.de/purl?PPN234788267" rel="nofollow">Lehrbuch der Algebra</a></i>, Vieweg<span class="printonly">, <a href="http://resolver.sub.uni-goettingen.de/purl?PPN234788267" class="external free" title="http://resolver.sub.uni-goettingen.de/purl?PPN234788267" rel="nofollow">http://resolver.sub.uni-goettingen.de/purl?PPN234788267</a></span></cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Lehrbuch+der+Algebra&amp;rft.aulast=Fricke&amp;rft.aufirst=Robert&amp;rft.au=Fricke%2C+Robert&amp;rft.au=Weber%2C+Heinrich+Martin&amp;rft.date=1924&amp;rft.pub=Vieweg&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fresolver.sub.uni-goettingen.de%2Fpurl%3FPPN234788267&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Field_(mathematics)"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-2"><b><a href="#cite_ref-2" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="" id="CITEREFSteinitz1910"><a href="/wiki/Ernst_Steinitz" title="Ernst Steinitz">Steinitz, Ernst</a> (1910), "<a href="http://resolver.sub.uni-goettingen.de/purl?GDZPPN002167042" class="external text" title="http://resolver.sub.uni-goettingen.de/purl?GDZPPN002167042" rel="nofollow">Algebraische Theorie der Körper</a>", <i><a href="/wiki/Journal_f%C3%BCr_die_reine_und_angewandte_Mathematik" title="Journal für die reine und angewandte Mathematik" class="mw-redirect">Journal für die reine und angewandte Mathematik</a></i> <b>137</b>: 167–309, <a href="/wiki/International_Standard_Serial_Number" title="International Standard Serial Number">ISSN</a> <a href="http://worldcat.org/issn/0075-4102" class="external text" title="http://worldcat.org/issn/0075-4102" rel="nofollow">0075-4102</a><span class="printonly">, <a href="http://resolver.sub.uni-goettingen.de/purl?GDZPPN002167042" class="external free" title="http://resolver.sub.uni-goettingen.de/purl?GDZPPN002167042" rel="nofollow">http://resolver.sub.uni-goettingen.de/purl?GDZPPN002167042</a></span></cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.atitle=Algebraische+Theorie+der+K%C3%B6rper&amp;rft.jtitle=%5B%5BJournal+f%C3%BCr+die+reine+und+angewandte+Mathematik%5D%5D&amp;rft.aulast=Steinitz&amp;rft.aufirst=Ernst&amp;rft.au=Steinitz%2C+Ernst&amp;rft.date=1910&amp;rft.volume=137&amp;rft.pages=167%E2%80%93309&amp;rft.issn=0075-4102&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fresolver.sub.uni-goettingen.de%2Fpurl%3FGDZPPN002167042&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Field_(mathematics)"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-3"><b><a href="#cite_ref-3" title="">^</a></b> As an inverse limit of <a href="/wiki/Discrete_group" title="Discrete group">finite discrete groups</a>, it is equipped with the <a href="/wiki/Limit_topology" title="Limit topology" class="mw-redirect">profinite topology</a>, making it a <a href="/wiki/Profinite_group" title="Profinite group">profinite topological group</a></li>
</ol>
